{{italic title}}
The '''''Michigan Mathematical Journal''''' (established 1952) is published by the mathematics department at the [[University of Michigan]].  An important early editor for the Journal was [[George Piranian]].

Historically, the Journal has been published a small number of times in a given year (currently four), in all areas of [[mathematics]].  The current Managing Editor is [[Mircea Mustaţă]].<ref>[http://www.math.lsa.umich.edu/mmj/ Michigan Mathematical Journal homepage]</ref>

